<tr>
        <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap><a href="download_script.php?src_id=1436">vimtips.zip</a></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap><b>2.1</b></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap><i>2002-11-19</i></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap>6.0</td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top"><i><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=92">Benji Fisher</a></i></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" width="2000">Do not run :helptags automatically.&nbsp;&nbsp;The user should install the docs (totd.txt) himself.&nbsp;&nbsp;The tag for vimtips.txt is still inserted automatically.<br>Reason:&nbsp;&nbsp;as long as this is the only script that automatically edits the tags file, there is no problem, but what if someone else tries the same trick?&nbsp;&nbsp;Each script runs :helptags, wiping out the other's customization, ...</td>
</tr>
